Coene Says ECB’s Rate Increase Was Not a One-Off, Trends Reports

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-04-13T11:14:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/coene-says-ecb-s-rate-increase-was-not-a-one-off-trends-reports.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Luc Coene said the central bank gave a clear
signal that last week’s rate increase wasn’t a one-off by saying
monetary policy remains supportive for economic growth and
employment, Trends reported, citing an interview.  Coene said the ECB expects the economic recovery will be
solid and inflationary pressures will continue to be manifest in
comning months, the weekly magazine said on its website.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
